critical_positive: I think asking questions and really listening to what the other person had to say. We were both polite and considerate with each other. We talked about general things without going too personal. This helped keep the conversation flowing and gave us plenty of room to navigate within the conversation.
critical_negative: I should have not assumed that my conversation partner was in his 40's or late 30's. In my mind, it kind of created some friction between us at the beginning of the conversation.
